# FutuRaM chemical-element mutual disjointness
#
# PURPOSE
#   The 80 direct subclasses of futuram:Element model distinct chemical
#   elements (Copper, Iron, Gold, ...). They are MUTUALLY DISJOINT in reality:
#   a single class cannot be both Copper and Iron. Asserting this lets the
#   ROBOT/ELK consistency check actually reason -- e.g. catch a served or
#   bridged class that ends up subClassOf two different elements, or an element
#   class accidentally folded under another. Without these axioms the run is an
#   IRI-hygiene check only (SHACL does the rest); with them it is semantic.
#
#   futuram:unknownElement is DELIBERATELY EXCLUDED from the disjointness set:
#   it is the residual / catch-all placeholder for unattributed element mass and
#   is permitted to co-occur with any concrete element (it is not a real,
#   mutually-exclusive element).
#
# EL-SAFETY
#   owl:AllDisjointClasses over named classes is within the OWL 2 EL profile and
#   is handled by ELK. No allValuesFrom / complementOf / negation / cardinality
#   is introduced here, so the consistency check stays inside EL (reasoner=elk).
#
# PROVENANCE
#   The member list is derived programmatically (scripts, rdflib) as the named
#   subjects of  rdfs:subClassOf futuram:Element  across composition-statement.ttl,
#   futuram-hierarchy.ttl and futuram-chebi-bridge.ttl, minus futuram:unknownElement.
#   Regenerate with the same query if the element roster changes.

@prefix futuram: <https://www.purl.org/futuram#> .
@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
@prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

<https://www.purl.org/futuram/element-disjointness> a owl:Ontology ;
    rdfs:label "FutuRaM Element Disjointness" .

[] a owl:AllDisjointClasses ;
    owl:members ( futuram:Actinium futuram:Aluminium futuram:Antimony futuram:Astatine futuram:Barium futuram:Beryllium futuram:Bismuth futuram:Boron futuram:Cadmium futuram:Calcium futuram:Carbon futuram:Cerium futuram:Chlorine futuram:Chromium futuram:Cobalt futuram:Copper futuram:Dysprosium futuram:Fluorine futuram:Gallium futuram:Germanium futuram:Gold futuram:Hafnium futuram:Hassium futuram:Helium futuram:Hydrogen futuram:Indium futuram:Iridium futuram:Iron futuram:Krypton futuram:Lanthanum futuram:Lawrencium futuram:Lead futuram:Lithium futuram:Lutetium futuram:Magnesium futuram:Manganese futuram:Mercury futuram:Molybdenum futuram:Neodymium futuram:Neon futuram:Nickel futuram:Niobium futuram:Nitrogen futuram:Osmium futuram:Oxygen futuram:Palladium futuram:Phosphorus futuram:Platinum futuram:Plutonium futuram:Polonium futuram:Potassium futuram:Praseodymium futuram:Radium futuram:Rhenium futuram:Rhodium futuram:Rubidium futuram:Ruthenium futuram:Scandium futuram:Selenium futuram:Silicon futuram:Silver futuram:Strontium futuram:Sulfur futuram:Tantalum futuram:Tellurium futuram:Tennessine futuram:Terbium futuram:Thallium futuram:Thorium futuram:Thulium futuram:Tin futuram:Titanium futuram:Tungsten futuram:Vanadium futuram:Xenon futuram:Ytterbium futuram:Yttrium futuram:Zinc futuram:Zirconium ) .

